 13, 2013</a></p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Wonderful cocktails last night. They were bitter and left a nasty taste in the mouth but just one had me laughing. Calling them 'Coal Miner'</p><p>&mdash; Iain Duncan Smith MP (@IDS_MP) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/IDS_MP/statuses/323015131619553280\">April 13, 2013</a></p></blockquote><p>David Cameron is not the first to be taken in by a spoof Twitter account. There are hundreds of them (as we speak, someone will be making a royal baby account). For the most part, spoof accounts are pretty bland, but occasionally one pops up that really nails the parody. Here are our top spoof tweeters: </p><h2><a href=\"https://twitter.com/KimKierkegaard\">@KimKierkegaard</a></h2><p>A mash-up of quotes from the Danish philosopher Søren Kierkegaard and reality TV celebrity Kim Kardashian work amazingly well. The author obviously spends a lot of time carefully putting the tweets together, and they rarely fail to crack me up. Sample tweets include: </p><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Send me pics of your best Kardashian Glow tan! So that we may glimpse the damage done to your soul.&mdash; KimKierkegaardashian (@KimKierkegaard) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KimKierkegaard/statuses/316373884930777089\">March 26, 2013</a></p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Are passions, then, the pagans of the soul? Is reason alone baptized? The sexy secretary look lets you have both.&mdash; KimKierkegaardashian (@KimKierkegaard) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KimKierkegaard/statuses/343231393268105216\">June 8, 2013</a></p></blockquote><h2><a href=\"https://twitter.com/DoritosOntario\">@DoritosOntario</a></h2><p>Most corporate accounts are boring, official and unimaginative (don't you dare say that about <a href=\"https://twitter.com/commentisfree\">@commentisfree</a>). So we welcome this parody account for Doritos in Canada. Might even make us buy their dusty orange crisps. Sample tweets include:</p><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Don't worry about the shape of Doritos similarity to illuminati symbology. Just don't worry about it. What's on TV?&mdash; Doritos Ontario (@DoritosOntario) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/DoritosOntario/statuses/355381313701818368\">July 11, 2013</a></p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Do you feed your pets Doritos? Send us a photo, but please dont tell the police we told you to feed your pet Doritos. But pls take a picture</p><p>&mdash; Doritos Ontario (@DoritosOntario) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/DoritosOntario/statuses/353349814458654720\">July 6, 2013</a></p></blockquote><h2><a href=\"https://twitter.com/FakeAPStylebook\">@FakeAPStylebook</a><br /></h2><p>Respected writers might use the AP stylebook to guide them on grammar and punctuation, but the smart people go straight to FakeAPStylebook. Likely to enrage purists, this account offers terrible advice for aspiring authors, but it's very funny. Sample tweets include:</p><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>If you wrote a column making a hilariously incorrect election prediction, an apology or resignat--ha ha just kidding, it's cool.&mdash; Fake AP Stylebook (@FakeAPStylebook) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/FakeAPStylebook/statuses/268444518976729088\">November 13, 2012</a></p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Baning - Using a Sean Connery impression to scare people. Don't confuse with \"boning,\" something else Sean Connery does better than you.&mdash; Fake AP Stylebook (@FakeAPStylebook) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/FakeAPStylebook/statuses/228866832277327873\">July 27, 2012</a></p></blockquote><h2><a href=\"https://twitter.com/MrsStephenFry\">@MrsStephenFry</a></h2><p>One of the original parody accounts, Mrs Fry pertains to be the long suffering wife of Stephen Fry, who helped boost her popularity by playing along. Since her early success, she's written a book, and come out of the shadows a little bit. Sample tweets include: </p><blockquo